The paper proposes a novel framework for answering science exam questions using contextual knowledge graphs and neural embeddings. This involves natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the arXiv CS sub-categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The use of knowledge graphs also suggests a potential association with Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper may involve computer vision techniques for processing supporting sentences, which could relate to Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV).
